main event: A round bright red object, the size of a penny held at arm's length, was observed for at least 1 1/2 hours at an elevation of 15 degrees in the northwest. The object was seen through binoculars of unknown power and was still in sight at the time of the report.
interesting points: The object was observed for a significant duration of 1 1/2 hours.
It was initially thought to be a UFO, but later confirmed to be the planet Venus due to its position in the sky.
Similar sightings had been observed on different dates by other witnesses.
The witness's description provides detailed information about the appearance and location of the object.
The report included the witness's name and contact information.
